# Feature Status and Lifecycle

Lifecycle for `F##` in `features-list.md` and `F##_*.md` frontmatter. Distinct from backlog item status (`Todo` / `In Progress` / `Done` on `BL-##`).

**Templates:** [features-list.md](../consultation/templates.md#features-listmd), [F##_ template](../consultation/templates.md#f_feature-slugmd)

## Status values

| Status | Meaning |
|--------|---------|
| **Draft** | Registered in inventory; spec not started |
| **Specifying** | `F##_*.md` exists with **Overview**; UR/FR, flows, or data model in progress |
| **Dev-ready** | All feature sections complete; passed architecture and cross-reference validation |
| **In development** | Implementation underway — ≥1 linked `BL-##` is `In Progress` or `Done` |
| **Implemented** | Every linked `BL-##` is `Done`; feature doc reflects shipped behaviour |
| **Cancelled** | Removed from scope; file kept until references cleared |

## Transition rules

| From | To | When |
|------|-----|------|
| — | **Draft** | Row added to `features-list.md` |
| **Draft** | **Specifying** | `F##_*.md` created with complete **Overview** |
| **Specifying** | **Dev-ready** | All sections complete; traces resolve; solution strategy ready ([04-solution-strategy.mdc](04-solution-strategy.mdc)); Must features map runtime to BB (or deferral in `open-questions.md` — no blocking `Q-A##`) |
| **Dev-ready** | **In development** | All **Requires** are **Implemented**; ≥1 linked `BL-##` is `In Progress` or `Done` |
| **In development** | **Implemented** | Every linked `BL-##` is `Done`; no blocking open questions |
| Any | **Cancelled** | Interview confirms drop — see [Removing a feature](#renaming-or-removing-a-feature) |

**Requires gate:** downstream features may reach **Dev-ready** while prerequisites are still in spec or dev; they cannot enter **In development** until every **Requires** is **Implemented**.

## Sync rules

| Field | Must match |
|-------|------------|
| `features-list.md` **Status** | `F##_*.md` frontmatter `status:` |
| **Requires** | frontmatter `requires`, Overview **Requires**, dependency diagram |
| Status change | Update list + frontmatter in one edit |

## Relationship to backlog

| Backlog state | Feature status implication |
|--------------|--------------------------|
| No `BL-##` or all `Todo` | Stay **Dev-ready** (or earlier) |
| ≥1 `BL-##` `In Progress` or `Done` | **In development** (if Requires gate passes) |
| All linked `BL-##` `Done` | **Implemented** |

When closing the last `BL-##`, set feature **Status** → **Implemented** in the same update pass.

## Adding a new feature

**Bulk inventory:** derive rows from goals and scenarios per [02-features-list.mdc](02-features-list.mdc).

**Single feature:**

1. Interview: name, scope, priority, stakeholders, primary user need — must link ≥1 `GOL-##` or `SCN-##`
2. Next `F##` from `features-list.md`
3. Row in `features-list.md` with **Traces to**, **Summary**, and **Status** `Draft`
4. Create `2-features/F##_slug.md` with **Overview** — set **Status** → `Specifying`
5. Complete spec sections; when validation passes, set **Status** → `Dev-ready`
6. Propagate: solution strategy ([04-solution-strategy.mdc](04-solution-strategy.mdc)) — pass ready gate — then building blocks, runtime flow; traceability, backlog, mockups/journeys if UI-heavy
7. Validate cross-references per [07-verification-validation-levels.mdc](07-verification-validation-levels.mdc)

## Renaming or removing a feature

1. Interview: confirm and migration plan
2. Set **Status** → `Cancelled`; resolve in-flight backlog items
3. Update all references (features-list, UR/FR, backlog, traceability, design, BB, runtime-views, NFR/ADR)
4. Delete feature file only after references cleared
5. Validate cross-references
